10
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,009
Today we observe the sounds a train makes.

11
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:45,005
This 'click-clack' noise. What's making it?

12
00:01:47,005 --> 00:01:51,008
We observe from outside the train.

13
00:01:59,003 --> 00:02:03,007
The 'click-clack' noise doesn't come from here.

14
00:02:07,007 --> 00:02:09,007
Let's try moving.

15
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:20,007
The 'click-clack' noise comes from here.

16
00:02:22,003 --> 00:02:28,000
How is this place different from the last?

17
00:02:28,001 --> 00:02:31,008
Let's try comparing the two places.

18
00:02:36,007 --> 00:02:39,004
If we pay close attention to the rails...

19
00:02:43,006 --> 00:02:48,006
Here, there's something attached to the rails.

20
00:02:50,008 --> 00:02:57,004
Let's observe the noise while watching this place closely

21
00:03:04,003 --> 00:03:07,002
Each time the train wheels pass here...

22
00:03:10,006 --> 00:03:13,008
We hear the noise.

23
00:03:13,008 --> 00:03:17,003
What on earth is this?

24
00:03:19,002 --> 00:03:21,004
If we look very carefully...

25
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:28,004
there's a gap in the rails.

26
00:03:28,004 --> 00:03:30,004
If we look from the side...

27
00:03:30,004 --> 00:03:34,001
The crack widens.

28
00:03:34,002 --> 00:03:39,009
Does the sound arise when the train wheels pass over this gap?

29
